<subSubSection id="C32ABD8E4045FFC3E2D2068D3444FAF5" pageId="30" pageNumber="181" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8FEE054045FFC3E2D2068D3444FAF5" blockId="30.[151,1437,1158,2011]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="B94432174045FFC3E2D2068D363BFB39" bold="true" box="[151,273,1158,1183]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Lorica outline oval, compressed dorso-ventrally, closed laterally, with dorsal and ventral indentations for head and foot. Retractable head shield present. Foot with four pseudosegments; foot and toes completely retractable in trunk. Two slender, moderately long toes with acutely pointed claw. Trophi malleo-virgate. Rami reduced, triangular with lateral alulae. Fulcrum fairly short, thin, straight and less high, without distal expansion. Unci a thin plate with five slender teeth of decreasing length; head of teeth free, tiny additional linear teeth present. Manubria long, straight, head reduced; cauda strongly expanded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
